⸻

7. Key Messaging for Conversions

Primary Direct Response Promises
	•	“Experience core outcome from your very first use.”
	•	“Made for people who demand value.”
	•	“Trusted by # customers.”

Pain-Point Messages
	•	“Struggle with pain? This fixes it by…”
	•	“If you’re tired of problem, here’s your solution…”

Benefit-Forward PDP Statements
	•	“Finally—desired result without frustration.”
	•	“Better category, built for everyday life.”

Objection Handlers
	•	“Try it risk-free for 30 days.”
	•	“Ships fast from our U.S. warehouse.”
	•	“Designed to last for years, not months.”

⸻

8. Common Questions & Objections

“Is it good quality?”

Answer: [Describe materials + durability]

“How long does it take to see results / feel a difference?”

Answer: [Set realistic expectations]

“How do I use it?”

Answer: [Explain simply + visually]

“What if it doesn’t work for me?”

Answer: [Guarantee + support process]

“How does it compare to cheaper alternatives?”

Answer: [Quality, sourcing, longevity, health, ethical standards]

⸻

9. Content Creation Guidelines for Physical Goods
	1.	Lead with outcomes customers care about.
	•	Not “Made from organic cotton.”
	•	But “Softer, breathable comfort that lasts all day.”
	2.	Use sensory language.
	•	Touch, smell, taste, feel, appearance.
	3.	Emphasize durability, safety, and trust.
	4.	Use real customer scenarios.
	5.	Address objections with clarity and confidence.
	6.	Always tie features → benefits → emotional payoff.
	7.	Highlight craftsmanship, quality, and brand values.

⸻

10. Versioning & Updates

Update this document when:
	•	New SKUs launch
	•	Materials or ingredients change
	•	Compliance or certifications update
	•	New bundles or upsells are introduced
	•	New testimonials or reviews become available

